{"article_id":"uP77YY2gTBtUbxgn","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Amid Fraud Allegations ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"North Carolina Election Board Wo n't Certify House Race","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Enough confusion has clouded a North Carolina congressional race","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"that the state 's board of elections has announced a delay","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"in certifying","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"that Republican Mark Harris defeated Democrat Dan McCready in the state 's 9th District","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"because of `` claims of irregularities and fraudulent activities . ''","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"In a 7-2 vote on Friday , the board said","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"it will instead hold a public hearing by Dec. 21","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"`` to assure","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"that the election is determined","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"without taint of fraud or corruption and without irregularities","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"that may have changed the result . ''","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"It follows a unanimous vote earlier this week","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"to postpone election certification results .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"The Friday vote fueled fresh uncertainty about the outcome of the race","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"and raised the possibility","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that a second election could be called .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"The two candidates are separated by 905 votes out of more than 280,000 cast ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"according to unofficial election results .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"The Associated Press originally called the race for Harris","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"but revoked that projection on Friday .","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"In a letter","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"sent to the board of elections ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"North Carolina 's Democratic Party made claims of wrongdoing .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"The Washington Post reported","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that the State Board of Elections and Ethics Enforcement has already collected at least six sworn statements from voters in Bladen County","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"alleging","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that people came to their doors","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"and urged them to hand over their absentee ballots .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"In Bladen and Robeson counties , some 3,400 absentee ballots failed to be mailed back to election officials ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"according to NPR member station WFAE .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"That equates to 40 percent of mail-in ballots in Bladen County and 64 percent in Robeson ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"according to a Raleigh News & Observer analysis .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Gerry Cohen , an elections expert in North Carolina , told WFAE","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"when people go through the process","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"to request an absentee ballot ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"they often return them .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"`` The return rate is usually about 80 or 90 percent , ''","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"November 's unreturned ballots were disproportionately associated with minorities ,","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"according to The News & Observer :","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"More than 40 percent of the ballots","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"requested by African Americans","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"and more than 60 percent of those","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"requested by American Indians","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"did not make it back to elections officials .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"For white voters , that figure was just 17 percent .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"In one affidavit","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"received by the board ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"a woman","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"named Emma Shipman","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"she was visited by a person","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"who claimed to be gathering absentee ballots ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"WFAE reported .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"Shipman said","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"she filled out the form","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"while the woman waited outside .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"`` She took the ballot","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and put it in an envelope","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"and never sealed it","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"or asked me to sign it .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Then she left . ''","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Collecting absentee ballots by a third party is illegal .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Shipman said ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"`` Because of the way","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"she presented herself ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"I thought","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"she was legitimate . ''","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"The candidates","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"running in North Carolina 's 9th Congressional District race","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"took opposing views of the election board 's postponement .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"`` I respect today 's decision by the bipartisan Board of Elections","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"to delay certification of our election results","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"until a full investigation is completed , ''","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Democratic candidate McCready said .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"He added ,","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"`` Any effort","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"to rob a person of that right","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"should be met with the full force of justice . ''","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Harris opposed the decision","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"and said ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"`` The State Board of Elections should act immediately","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to certify the race","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"while continuing to conduct their investigation .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Anything else is a disservice to the people of the Ninth District . ''","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"he supported efforts","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"to investigate allegations of voter fraud ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"`` as long as it is fair","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"and focuses on all political parties . ''","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Harris said","depth":5},{"id":95,"text":"there were not enough ballots in question","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"to affect the outcome of the race .","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"The board 's decision triggered Dallas Woodhouse , executive director of the North Carolina Republican Party , to call for the Democratic chairman of the state election board to resign .","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that Andy Penry , the chairman , `` has shown himself to be hyper-partisan ''","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"and that `` no public evidence in # CD9 shows vote tampering","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"and mathematically this could not have changed the race . ''","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Penry resigned on Saturday ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"he did not want his partisan views to be used","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"to undermine the investigation .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"`` The investigation of criminal conduct and absentee voting fraud in the 2018 Republican primary and 2018 general election in congressional District 9 is a matter of vital importance to our democracy , ''","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"he wrote in a statement ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"according to The Washington Post .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"`` I will not allow myself to be used as an instrument of distraction in this investigation . ''","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"The board convened for three hours on Friday by teleconference ,","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"WFAE reported .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"Two of four Republicans","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"serving on the board","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"- Ken Raymond and John Hemphill -","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"voted against the delay .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"The other two , Stacy Eggers and John Lewis , voted in line with the Democrats .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"The election board itself also faces uncertainty .","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"A panel of three judges ruled in October","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"that changes to the board","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"introduced by the state 's Republican-controlled General Assembly","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"were unconstitutional .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"North Carolina 's governor , Democrat Roy Cooper , said","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"the changes were designed to erode his control of the board .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"A stay in the ruling","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"that permitted the board to operate","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"was set to expire","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"but has been extended .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Harris filed a motion","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"for the board to remain in existence","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"until his race is certified .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":261,"left":132,"right":260,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":132,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":260,"left":201,"right":259,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":151,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":149,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":147,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":144,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":142,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":136,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclear